---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/services/advisory.css";
---

<Layout>
  <main class="service-page advisory-page">
    <section class="service-page-hero">
      <div class="service-page-shell">
        <p class="service-page-eyebrow">advisory</p>
        <h1>Guidance for what comes next.</h1>
        <p class="service-page-lead">Business decisions rarely fit neatly into a tax return or financial statement. We help owners think through the numbers, risks, and tradeoffs before making important decisions.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-page-intro">
      <div class="service-page-shell service-page-two-column">
        <div>
          <p class="service-page-kicker">How we help</p>
          <h2>A practical sounding board for business owners</h2>
        </div>
        <p>Advisory work can be formal or informal. Sometimes it is a projection or cash-flow analysis. Sometimes it is a conversation about hiring, financing, technology, compensation, or succession. The goal is the same: better decisions with fewer blind spots.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-page-offerings">
      <div class="service-page-shell">
        <div class="service-page-section-heading">
          <p class="service-page-kicker">Services</p>
          <h2>Support built around what you need.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="service-page-grid">
          <article class="service-page-offering">
            <h3>Cash-flow and projections</h3>
            <p>Forecasting and scenario analysis to understand what a decision may mean for the business.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="service-page-offering">
            <h3>Entity and compensation planning</h3>
            <p>Evaluation of business structure, owner compensation, and the tax and administrative consequences.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="service-page-offering">
            <h3>Technology and workflow</h3>
            <p>Guidance on accounting, payroll, document, and reporting systems that support a more efficient operation.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="service-page-offering">
            <h3>Growth and transition planning</h3>
            <p>Support for expansion, financing, succession, sale, or other major changes in the business.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-page-questions">
      <div class="service-page-shell service-page-two-column">
        <div>
          <p class="service-page-kicker">Common questions</p>
          <h2>Start with the question in front of you.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="service-page-question-list">
          <article class="service-page-question">
            <h3>What does advisory mean in practice?</h3>
            <p>It means helping you work through a decision using the financial, tax, and operational information available.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="service-page-question">
            <h3>Do I need ongoing advisory services?</h3>
            <p>Not necessarily. Some clients benefit from recurring meetings, while others need help only when a major decision arises.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="service-page-question">
            <h3>Can you help evaluate a purchase or expansion?</h3>
            <p>Yes. We can help model the expected cash flow, financing, tax impact, and risks.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-page-cta">
      <div class="service-page-shell service-page-cta-inner">
        <div>
          <p class="service-page-kicker">Let's talk</p>
          <h2>Need help with advisory?</h2>
          <p>Tell us what you are working through. We will help you determine the next practical step.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/contact">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
